-(GROWLS)

208
00:22:16.771 --> 00:22:18.906
-THIA: Oh. boy.
-(SQUAWKS)

209
00:22:19.674 --> 00:22:21.309
This isn't great for you.

210
00:22:21.374 --> 00:22:23.611
(SHRIEKS)

211
00:22:26.479 --> 00:22:31.351
(SCREECHING)

212
00:22:31.418 --> 00:22:32.787
(THUD)

213
00:22:35.289 --> 00:22:37.058
(GRUNTS)

214
00:22:38.793 --> 00:22:41.829
-(HISSING)
-(GRUMBLES)

215
00:22:41.896 --> 00:22:44.565
THIA: It waits
for the needles to paralyze you.

216
00:22:45.432 --> 00:22:48.236
Then eats you
while you can't move.

217
00:22:48.302 --> 00:22:50.872
(GROANS. ROARS. CLICKING)

218
00:22:55.343 --> 00:22:59.780
I could help you. but...
I need a hand.

219
00:23:00.380 --> 00:23:02.783
(CHUFFS. GRUNTS)

220
00:23:04.118 --> 00:23:06.254
(GRUNTS)

221
00:23:06.554 --> 00:23:08.723
(IN YAUTJA)

222
00:23:08.789 --> 00:23:13.027
Yautja might hunt alone.
but they die alone too.

223
00:23:13.094 --> 00:23:15.730
(CHITTERING. GRUNTING)

224
00:23:16.197 --> 00:23:18.566
-Kalisk.
-(WHICKERS)

225
00:23:20.902 --> 00:23:23.905
-You're hunting the Kalisk.
-(METALLIC CLANG)

226
00:23:23.971 --> 00:23:26.007
(SHRIEKS)

227
00:23:26.073 --> 00:23:27.474
(THUD)

228
00:23:29.310 --> 00:23:31.112
(GASPING)

229
00:23:31.178 --> 00:23:32.313
(ROARS ANGRILY)

230
00:23:32.380 --> 00:23:33.446
(GRUNTS)

231
00:23:33.514 --> 00:23:35.016
(THORNS RICOCHETING)

232
00:23:35.650 --> 00:23:37.618
Gotta run faster.

233
00:23:39.353 --> 00:23:40.855
(GRUNTS. GASPS)

234
00:23:40.922 --> 00:23:42.890
(ROARS)

235
00:23:44.592 --> 00:23:46.426
THIA: It happens fast. huh?

236
00:23:46.493 --> 00:23:47.962
(PANTING)

237
00:23:48.029 --> 00:23:51.165
THIA: If you had a weapon.
you know. I could use it.

238
00:23:51.532 --> 00:23:53.634
(BEEPING)

239
00:23:55.036 --> 00:23:57.405
THIA: Throw me that.
and I can get you the antidote.

240
00:23:57.470 --> 00:23:59.974
-(BREATHING HEAVILY)
-(SHRIEKS)

241
00:24:00.041 --> 00:24:01.509
THIA: Now or never.

242
00:24:03.077 --> 00:24:05.212
(METALLIC WARBLING)

243
00:24:06.147 --> 00:24:07.480
(STRAINED GRUNTS)

244
00:24:09.817 --> 00:24:12.620
(GRUNTS)

245
00:24:13.287 --> 00:24:15.523
(GRUNTS)

246
00:24:18.859 --> 00:24:21.062
-(GROANS)
-(CREATURE SCREECHES)

247
00:24:26.466 --> 00:24:29.437
(CREATURE SQUAWKS)

248
00:24:29.503 --> 00:24:31.539
(ROARS)

249
00:24:32.139 --> 00:24:33.975
-(BLOWS LANDING)
-(CREATURE SQUAWKING)

250
00:24:34.041 --> 00:24:37.979
-(METALLIC STABBING)
-(SQUEALING)

251
00:24:39.046 --> 00:24:41.115
(PANTING) Hi.

252
00:24:44.352 --> 00:24:47.088
(SPEECH IN YAUTJA ECHOES)

253
00:24:49.690 --> 00:24:51.926
(BREATHING DEEPLY)

254
00:25:03.337 --> 00:25:05.706
THIA: Should be good as new.

255
00:25:06.107 --> 00:25:07.842
(GRUNTS)

256
00:25:10.678 --> 00:25:12.446
The venom makes them bloom.

257
00:25:12.513 --> 00:25:14.882
Also makes them
a handy antidote.

258
00:25:15.616 --> 00:25:16.984
(GRUNTS)

259
00:25:21.389 --> 00:25:23.057
How about a lift?

260
00:25:26.093 --> 00:25:28.129
-(LIGHT GROWL)
-Let's go.

261
00:25:31.098 --> 00:25:31.966
(GROWLS)

262
00:25:32.033 --> 00:25:33.734
Excuse you. sir.

263
00:25:36.670 --> 00:25:38.739
I'm synthetic.
I was built and deployed

264
00:25:38.806 --> 00:25:41.409
by the Weyland-Yutani
Corporation for research.

265
00:25:41.475 --> 00:25:44.345
Because their humans wouldn't
last a day on this planet.

266
00:25:44.412 --> 00:25:45.514
(CHUCKLES)
We found that--

267
00:25:45.579 --> 00:25:47.314
(THUDS)

268
00:25:47.381 --> 00:25:48.816
(SIGHS)

269
00:25:50.451 --> 00:25:52.253
(GRUNTS)

270
00:25:52.319 --> 00:25:54.121
Look... (SIGHS)

271
00:25:54.188 --> 00:25:57.526
Many Yautja have come
for the great Kalisk.

272
00:25:57.591 --> 00:26:00.094
and none have survived it...

273
00:26:00.161 --> 00:26:01.662
or Genna.

274
00:26:02.363 --> 00:26:03.697
(SIGHS)

275
00:26:04.598 --> 00:26:06.700
I've seen the Kalisk.

276
00:26:07.134 --> 00:26:08.602
I survived it.

277
00:26:09.538 --> 00:26:12.573
Here's my proposal:
You take me along with you.

278
00:26:12.640 --> 00:26:15.242
and I'll guide you to its den.

279
00:26:15.309 --> 00:26:17.645
Once there. I get my legs.

280
00:26:17.711 --> 00:26:19.413
you get your trophy.

281
00:26:19.480 --> 00:26:22.783
and everyone's a winner. Deal?

282
00:26:28.456 --> 00:26:32.693
Oh. yeah. I've seen the Kalisk.

283
00:26:35.429 --> 00:26:36.797
(SCOFFS)

284
00:26:37.364 --> 00:26:39.333
(DEVICE BEEPS. WHIRS)

285
00:26:39.400 --> 00:26:43.070
(SIGHS)

286
00:26:44.338 --> 00:26:45.873
Okay. Hmm.

287
00:26:46.874 --> 00:26:49.009
-(GROWLS)
-(THIA SIGHS)

288
00:26:49.076 --> 00:26:51.078
Good luck with your journey.

289
00:26:52.046 --> 00:26:56.250
I'm just gonna...
go on my journey.

290
00:26:58.152 --> 00:27:00.354
I'm sure
you'll figure something out.

291
00:27:07.261 --> 00:27:10.030
Hey. (PANTING)

292
00:27:11.065 --> 00:27:14.301
I've already shown you
that I can be useful to you.

293
00:27:20.040 --> 00:27:24.078
Yes. Yes. exactly. like a tool.

294
00:27:24.145 --> 00:27:26.747
The only way to survive Genna
is to work with it.

295
00:27:26.814 --> 00:27:28.617
and I know how.

296
00:27:28.682 --> 00:27:31.986
And with the right tool...

297
00:27:33.387 --> 00:27:35.222
...you could get the Kalisk.

298
00:27:35.890 --> 00:27:37.358
You could be the first.

299
00:27:42.663 --> 00:27:45.166
You may call me Thi-- Whoa!

300
00:27:46.066 --> 00:27:50.371
You seem smaller than the other
Yautja. How old are you?

301
00:27:51.640 --> 00:27:53.107
And what does the chewing?

302
00:27:53.174 --> 00:27:55.910
Your outside fangs
or your inside teeth?

303
00:27:57.478 --> 00:28:00.147
Oh. What should I call you?

304
00:28:03.717 --> 00:28:05.319
-(GRUNTS)
-(YELPS)

305
00:28:05.953 --> 00:28:07.656
Whoa! (LAUGHS)

306
00:28:07.755 --> 00:28:10.592
I've never been thrown before.
What a... (DISTORTS) ...thrill!

307
00:28:10.659 --> 00:28:13.060
How fast were you going
when your ship crashed?

308
00:28:13.127 --> 00:28:16.397
Faster than sub-light speed?
We haven't cracked that yet.

309
00:28:16.463 --> 00:28:18.899
Also. that plasma sword
is interesting.

310
00:28:18.966 --> 00:28:20.501
Is it unique to your clan?

311
00:28:20.569 --> 00:28:21.802
And what may I call you?

312
00:28:22.671 --> 00:28:25.940
-I call these <i>imbre anguis.</i>
-(PROJECTILES HISSING)

313
00:28:35.617 --> 00:28:37.619
(PANTING)

314
00:28:37.686 --> 00:28:39.386
THIA: They just want a snack.

315
00:28:43.724 --> 00:28:46.427
(SQUEAKING)

316
00:28:46.493 --> 00:28:49.797
You catch more flies with honey
than you do with vinegar.

317
00:28:49.863 --> 00:28:51.865
(BUZZING)

318
00:28:53.367 --> 00:28:57.271
Predatory organisms are
my specific area of expertise.

319
00:28:57.338 --> 00:29:00.808
I've studied Yautja extensively.
It's an impressive culture.

320
00:29:00.874 --> 00:29:02.243
(SIGHS)

321
00:29:02.309 --> 00:29:04.512
Here. ask me anything.
I bet I have the answer.

322
00:29:04.579 --> 00:29:05.946
-(EXHALES)
-Oh! (THUDS)

323
00:29:06.013 --> 00:29:07.381
(ANIMALS CALL DISTANTLY)

324
00:29:07.448 --> 00:29:08.782
Very funny.

325
00:29:08.849 --> 00:29:10.818
And you still haven't
told me your name.

326
00:29:36.745 --> 00:29:38.613
Okay. sure.

327
00:29:39.113 --> 00:29:43.417
(SIGHS) Well. let's back up
and start at the beginning.

328
00:29:43.752 --> 00:29:46.621
Genna was formed
64 billion cycles ago.

329
00:29:46.688 --> 00:29:49.857
when a dying red dwarf star
in a neighboring system...

330
00:29:49.923 --> 00:29:52.159
(BEEPING)

331
00:29:57.264 --> 00:29:59.500
(WHIRRING)

332
00:30:01.001 --> 00:30:02.604
(CLICKING. WHIRRING)

333
00:30:02.671 --> 00:30:04.673
It's so beautiful.

334
00:30:05.172 --> 00:30:07.841
After all the time
I've been stuck here.

335
00:30:07.908 --> 00:30:10.144
I never get tired of the view.

336
00:30:13.581 --> 00:30:17.284
Well. we arrived on Genna two
years ago. and we built a base.

337
00:30:17.351 --> 00:30:19.953
Then. I was in
the vulture's nest

338
00:30:20.020 --> 00:30:21.822
for the most exciting

339
00:30:21.889 --> 00:30:25.025
13 days. seven hours. 43 minutes

340
00:30:25.092 --> 00:30:27.194
and two seconds of my life.

341
00:30:27.261 --> 00:30:28.462
(EXHALES)

342
00:30:28.530 --> 00:30:30.864
But I always knew
someone would come.

343
00:30:31.700 --> 00:30:34.134
I was just wrong about who.

344
00:30:40.675 --> 00:30:42.142
Tessa.

345
00:30:43.377 --> 00:30:47.014
Our crew is made up
entirely of synths.

346
00:30:47.081 --> 00:30:48.949
But Tessa and I are special.

347
00:30:49.450 --> 00:30:52.152
We have a higher sensitivity
than the others.

348
00:30:57.692 --> 00:31:00.027
Sensitivity is what allows us
to understand

349
00:31:00.094 --> 00:31:02.196
the creatures on this planet.

350
00:31:05.567 --> 00:31:07.935
We were created
to work in tandem.

351
00:31:08.603 --> 00:31:12.607
Me. cooped up in the lab.
Tessa out in the field.

352
00:31:12.674 --> 00:31:16.176
Until the wonderful day
Tessa let me come with her.

353
00:31:16.243 --> 00:31:18.613
We were exploring Genna.

354
00:31:19.913 --> 00:31:23.217
And then the Kalisk attacked us.

355
00:31:24.118 --> 00:31:27.856
Separated me... and us.

356
00:31:30.190 --> 00:31:33.227
The last sound
I remember hearing

357
00:31:33.293 --> 00:31:36.964
was Tessa calling out my name.

358
00:31:37.532 --> 00:31:39.233
Reaching for me.

359
00:31:40.901 --> 00:31:42.936
Then the Kalisk.

360
00:31:43.904 --> 00:31:45.640
I didn't know what to do.

361
00:31:46.841 --> 00:31:50.512
(DEK SNORING)

362
00:31:56.618 --> 00:31:59.554
But I refuse
to believe she's dead.

363
00:32:01.890 --> 00:32:07.194
(BEEPING)

364
00:32:12.166 --> 00:32:16.838
(HYDRAULICS HISSING)

365
00:32:16.905 --> 00:32:18.005
(THUDS)

366
00:32:19.072 --> 00:32:21.308
(WHIRRING)

367
00:32:25.312 --> 00:32:27.381
-(CLICKS)
-(ELECTRONIC WARBLE)

368
00:32:35.155 --> 00:32:37.391
Thia. Thia. Thia. Thia.

369
00:32:37.458 --> 00:32:38.125
(GUNFIRE)

370
00:32:38.192 --> 00:32:40.728
Thia. Thia. Thia...

371
00:32:41.361 --> 00:32:43.798
THIA: <i>Tessa!</i> (YELLING)

372
00:32:43.865 --> 00:32:44.766
(ROARS)

373
00:32:45.165 --> 00:32:47.669
Thia. Thia. Thia. Thia.

374
00:32:47.735 --> 00:32:49.069
Thia. Thia.

375
00:32:49.136 --> 00:32:52.339
(WHIRRING)

376
00:32:58.513 --> 00:33:00.447
(WHIRRING)

377
00:33:08.523 --> 00:33:10.558
(BUZZING)

378
00:33:20.033 --> 00:33:22.102
(ELECTRONIC CHIRPING)

379
00:33:22.169 --> 00:33:24.404
(GASPS)

380
00:33:26.106 --> 00:33:28.242
(WHIRRING)

381
00:33:28.743 --> 00:33:30.745
MUTHUR: <i>Hello. Tessa.</i>

382
00:33:30.812 --> 00:33:33.515
<i>The Company is not pleased.</i>

383
00:33:34.983 --> 00:33:38.686
<i>Continued failure will result</i>
<i>in your decommission.</i>

384
00:33:42.155 --> 00:33:44.191
Where's Thia?

385
00:33:47.261 --> 00:33:49.429
MUTHUR: <i>The Yautja has Thia.</i>

386
00:33:52.800 --> 00:33:56.270
(CREATURES CHITTERING)

387
00:33:58.071 --> 00:34:00.474
(CAWING)

388
00:34:00.542 --> 00:34:02.577
(IN YAUTJA)

389
00:34:02.644 --> 00:34:06.046
THIA: Two warriors.
Dek and Thia. on the hunt.

390
00:34:06.548 --> 00:34:07.949
Oh.

391
00:34:08.016 --> 00:34:09.751
Quick question.

392
00:34:09.817 --> 00:34:11.084
What should I be doing?

393
00:34:11.151 --> 00:34:12.854
(CHUFFS)

394
00:34:12.921 --> 00:34:14.622
(ANIMAL GROWLS)

395
00:34:18.593 --> 00:34:21.461
THIA: Bone bison.
They're Kalisk food.

396
00:34:21.529 --> 00:34:22.997
(GROWLING)

397
00:34:23.063 --> 00:34:26.500
DEK:

398
00:34:26.568 --> 00:34:30.103
So exciting.
Hunting with a Yautja.

399
00:34:30.170 --> 00:34:31.204
-(GROWLS)
-Tessa wouldn't believe it.

400
00:34:31.271 --> 00:34:32.740
(CHUFFS. CLICKS)

401
00:34:33.641 --> 00:34:35.309
-Just a warning...
-(GROWLS)

402
00:34:38.078 --> 00:34:39.514
(YELPS. GROWLS)

403
00:34:40.213 --> 00:34:41.415
(QUIETLY) Razor grass.

404
00:34:41.481 --> 00:34:42.717
(CLINKS)

405
00:34:44.719 --> 00:34:47.755
It'll cut you to ribbons.
We'll just go around.

406
00:34:54.394 --> 00:34:56.496
(CREATURE CHITTERING)

407
00:34:56.731 --> 00:34:59.366
We might not be alone
in this hunt.

408
00:35:00.500 --> 00:35:02.804
(BEEPING)

409
00:35:02.870 --> 00:35:04.271
(WHIRRING)

410
00:35:05.840 --> 00:35:08.342
-(HISSES)
-(SHOUTS)

411
00:35:09.409 --> 00:35:10.945
What an odd critter.

412
00:35:11.012 --> 00:35:13.213
I've never seen you before.

413
00:35:13.548 --> 00:35:14.649
(HISSES)

414
00:35:15.783 --> 00:35:17.652
(ROARS)

415
00:35:18.452 --> 00:35:20.622
Thia. Nice to meet you.

416
00:35:21.055 --> 00:35:22.757
-(SCOFFS)
-(SPRINGING CLICK)

417
00:35:22.824 --> 00:35:24.358
(GRUNTS)

418
00:35:25.059 --> 00:35:27.662
(GROWLS. ROARS)

419
00:35:34.201 --> 00:35:35.670
(CLICKING)

420
00:35:35.737 --> 00:35:37.572
Looks like your competition
is better-- (GASPS)

421
00:35:37.639 --> 00:35:39.607
(GROWLING)

422
00:35:55.023 --> 00:35:57.959
Careful up in these trees.
There are Luna bugs!

423
00:35:58.026 --> 00:35:59.226
-(THIA YELPS)
-(DEK GRUNTS)

424
00:36:00.695 --> 00:36:04.464
(STRAINED GROANS)

425
00:36:04.532 --> 00:36:06.901
(GASPING)

426
00:36:06.968 --> 00:36:09.904
(FOOTSTEPS RUMBLING)

427
00:36:09.971 --> 00:36:12.840
(ROARS)

428
00:36:12.907 --> 00:36:14.642
(BONE BISON ROARS)

429
00:36:19.147 --> 00:36:20.414
THIA: Coming up behind you!

430
00:36:20.480 --> 00:36:22.517
-(CHITTERS)
-(ROARS)

431
00:36:23.084 --> 00:36:25.318
(CHITTERING)

432
00:36:27.354 --> 00:36:29.189
(CREATURE SHRIEKS)

433
00:36:30.091 --> 00:36:32.325
(BOTH GRUNTING)

434
00:36:32.660 --> 00:36:33.528
(GRUNTS)

435
00:36:34.162 --> 00:36:35.663
THIA: Stronger than it looks!

436
00:36:42.436 --> 00:36:43.938
(GAGS. SHRIEKS)

437
00:36:45.506 --> 00:36:48.408
-(SCREECHES)
-Uh. Dek?

438
00:36:48.475 --> 00:36:51.112
-(YELPS)
-Dek! Look!

439
00:36:51.179 --> 00:36:52.547
(CREATURE ROARS)

440
00:36:55.282 --> 00:36:56.751
(GROWLS)

441
00:36:58.385 --> 00:37:00.420
(TRUMPETS)

442
00:37:01.522 --> 00:37:03.658
(SLOWED METALLIC SCRAPE)

443
00:37:15.737 --> 00:37:19.607
(SQUELCHING)

444
00:37:23.945 --> 00:37:24.979
(GRUNTS)

445
00:37:28.248 --> 00:37:29.784
(ROARS)

446
00:37:31.085 --> 00:37:32.920
(THIA YELLS)

447
00:37:36.490 --> 00:37:37.892
THIA: Not a Kalisk.

448
00:37:40.061 --> 00:37:42.163
This is a Luna bug!

449
00:37:42.230 --> 00:37:44.766
(RUMBLING)

450
00:37:44.832 --> 00:37:46.701
(DEEP CHITTERING)

451
00:37:48.368 --> 00:37:50.104
(ROARS)

452
00:37:50.171 --> 00:37:51.506
THIA: Have any other weapons?

453
00:37:51.572 --> 00:37:53.040
(METALLIC CLINKING. BEEPING)

454
00:37:54.008 --> 00:37:57.277
(LUNA BUG GROWLING)

455
00:38:01.414 --> 00:38:03.951
-(SCREECHES)
-(CRUNCHING)

456
00:38:04.018 --> 00:38:06.988
-(CREATURE GROWLS)
-(THIA YELLING)

457
00:38:07.054 --> 00:38:09.891
(GRUNTS)

458
00:38:13.828 --> 00:38:17.131
-(INHALES. GRUNTS)
-(CREATURE SQUAWKS)

459
00:38:17.198 --> 00:38:20.668
-(GROWLS)
-(MURMURS)

460
00:38:20.735 --> 00:38:22.369
(ROARS)

461
00:38:23.137 --> 00:38:26.007
(ROARING)

462
00:38:26.774 --> 00:38:27.809
(SNARLS)

463
00:38:32.713 --> 00:38:35.650
-(PANTING)
-(ROARS)

464
00:38:37.317 --> 00:38:39.386
(CHITTERING)

465
00:38:40.588 --> 00:38:42.723
-(PANTING)
-(SHRIEKS)

466
00:38:44.324 --> 00:38:46.393
(GROWLING)

467
00:38:46.459 --> 00:38:48.461
(FOOTSTEPS THUNDERING)

468
00:38:48.529 --> 00:38:50.731
Why'd you stop?
Let's get out of here.

469
00:38:54.334 --> 00:38:56.469
(CRACKLING)

470
00:38:57.905 --> 00:39:00.373
(CHITTERING)

471
00:39:05.079 --> 00:39:06.413
(ROARS)

472
00:39:07.882 --> 00:39:09.416
(ROARS)

473
00:39:11.586 --> 00:39:15.122
(FEARFUL CHITTERING)

474
00:39:23.130 --> 00:39:25.398
(GROWLS)

475
00:39:27.969 --> 00:39:29.804
(ROARS)

476
00:39:31.739 --> 00:39:34.876
(CHITTERS. MURMURS)

477
00:39:43.251 --> 00:39:46.921
(PANTING)

478
00:39:48.990 --> 00:39:51.792
(ANIMALS CHIRP. CHITTER)

479
00:39:55.830 --> 00:39:57.698
(CHIRPS)

480
00:40:13.581 --> 00:40:15.650
(SCREECHING)

481
00:40:18.451 --> 00:40:20.621
(CHITTERS. SCREECHES)

482
00:40:30.998 --> 00:40:32.133
(GUN CLICKS)

483
00:40:37.872 --> 00:40:39.073
(CHITTERS)

484
00:40:39.640 --> 00:40:41.075
(SCREECHES)

485
00:40:41.976 --> 00:40:43.476
(FLAMES ROARING)

486
00:40:43.778 --> 00:40:45.680
That was the best hunt
I've ever been on.

487
00:40:45.746 --> 00:40:47.315
This is the dream team
right here.

488
00:40:47.381 --> 00:40:49.717
The Dynamic Three.
The Dynamic Trio.

489
00:40:49.784 --> 00:40:51.585
The Dynamic Tree-oh!

490
00:40:51.652 --> 00:40:53.754
Tree-oh! Remember when
we went down the tree?

491
00:40:53.821 --> 00:40:55.556
That monster's mouth.
I mean...

492
00:40:55.623 --> 00:40:57.024
(DISGUSTED MOAN)

493
00:40:57.091 --> 00:40:58.960
Didn't smell great.
didn't smell great. But...

494
00:40:59.026 --> 00:41:00.227
(THIA SIGHS)

495
00:41:00.294 --> 00:41:02.897
We got him. We got him.
And then we met you.

496
00:41:02.964 --> 00:41:05.700
our little sweet.
little. little thing.

497
00:41:05.766 --> 00:41:08.302
Thank you. seriously.
for that experience.

498
00:41:08.369 --> 00:41:10.871
Truly amazing. Thrilling.

499
00:41:10.938 --> 00:41:13.507
Truly thrilling.
What was your favorite part?

500
00:41:13.574 --> 00:41:15.943
-(CHITTERS)
-(WHICKERS)

501
00:41:16.544 --> 00:41:20.514
(IN YAUTJA)

502
00:41:26.620 --> 00:41:27.922
Cool.

503
00:41:29.256 --> 00:41:31.726
(CHITTERS SOFTLY)

504
00:41:36.097 --> 00:41:40.534
Oh. No. thanks. I don't eat.
but that's very sweet.

505
00:41:45.673 --> 00:41:47.041
Good to know.

506
00:41:47.308 --> 00:41:49.977
(CHITTERS. SQUEAKS)

507
00:41:50.444 --> 00:41:51.345
(STOPS)

508
00:41:51.946 --> 00:41:54.115
Our little bud here
looks hungry.

509
00:41:56.517 --> 00:41:57.752
(DEK CHUFFS)

510
00:41:58.886 --> 00:42:00.021
(SQUEAKS)

511
00:42:03.724 --> 00:42:05.626
(SPITS. CHITTERS)

512
00:42:05.693 --> 00:42:06.660
(ROARS)

513
00:42:06.727 --> 00:42:08.662
I think she's marking you.

514
00:42:08.996 --> 00:42:11.532
She wants you
to be a part of her clan.

515
00:42:12.166 --> 00:42:13.334
(MUNCHES)

516
00:42:13.401 --> 00:42:14.535
Maybe she's lost.

517
00:42:16.704 --> 00:42:20.674
What do you mean?
Don't all Yautja have family?

518
00:42:24.278 --> 00:42:26.847
So you never had anyone
looking out for you?

519
00:42:32.586 --> 00:42:33.687
Had?

520
00:42:36.690 --> 00:42:38.159
What happened to him?

521
00:42:46.500 --> 00:42:48.002
You're grieving.

522
00:42:48.369 --> 00:42:49.603
(CHITTERS)

523
00:42:55.142 --> 00:42:57.878
You're here
because you lost your brother.

524
00:43:10.691 --> 00:43:12.259
I'm here
because traveling with you

525
00:43:12.326 --> 00:43:14.995
is the best way
to get back to Tessa.

526
00:43:16.764 --> 00:43:18.265
When I was
in that vulture's nest.

527
00:43:18.332 --> 00:43:21.235
I was so afraid
I would never see her again.

528
00:43:26.207 --> 00:43:28.609
I can survive on my own.

529
00:43:29.777 --> 00:43:32.313
But who would want
to survive on their own?

530
00:43:40.421 --> 00:43:41.989
(WHICKERS)

531
00:43:44.325 --> 00:43:45.860
Sister.

532
00:43:48.629 --> 00:43:49.897
Yeah.

533
00:43:50.498 --> 00:43:52.266
I guess she is.

534
00:43:53.901 --> 00:43:57.338
I have... a sister.

535
00:43:58.172 --> 00:43:59.306
(CHUCKLES)

536
00:43:59.940 --> 00:44:02.143
What a lovely thought.

537
00:44:06.881 --> 00:44:08.682
I need to find her.

538
00:44:13.187 --> 00:44:14.722
Excuse me?

539
00:44:22.496 --> 00:44:24.098
Was that a joke?

540
00:44:24.533 --> 00:44:27.968
-(WHICKERS)
-(CHUCKLES)

541
00:44:40.748 --> 00:44:42.783
(WHICKERS. CHUFFS)

542
00:44:48.422 --> 00:44:49.823
(GRUNTS)

543
00:44:56.230 --> 00:44:58.265
(YAWNING)

544
00:44:59.066 --> 00:45:02.303
(YAWNING)

545
00:45:04.539 --> 00:45:05.773
(CHUFFS)

546
00:45:10.844 --> 00:45:13.347
-(ELECTRONIC HUMMING)
-(CHUFFS)

547
00:45:19.588 --> 00:45:21.722
(MURMURS)

548
00:45:22.456 --> 00:45:23.658
(CHITTERS)

549
00:45:23.724 --> 00:45:25.159
(METALLIC SCRAPE)

550
00:45:25.660 --> 00:45:27.428
(ENGINES WHIRRING)

551
00:45:29.430 --> 00:45:30.864
(WHIRRING SLOWS)

552
00:45:44.579 --> 00:45:46.847
(WHIRRING)

553
00:45:51.352 --> 00:45:52.486
(THUDS)

554
00:46:10.771 --> 00:46:12.840
(BEEPING. CHIRPING)

555
00:46:29.857 --> 00:46:31.925
(ELECTRONIC BEEPING)

556
00:46:32.993 --> 00:46:34.461
(METALLIC SCRAPING)

557
00:46:42.002 --> 00:46:43.571
(THUDS. RUMBLES)

558
00:46:48.175 --> 00:46:49.910
(CLANKS)

559
00:47:23.645 --> 00:47:25.846
(CLICKS. HISSES)

560
00:47:43.364 --> 00:47:44.431
(IN YAUTJA)

561
00:47:46.601 --> 00:47:48.268
We can't leave Bud.

562
00:47:48.803 --> 00:47:50.037
Bud?

563
00:47:50.104 --> 00:47:53.374
-Yeah. Bud. I named her.
-(BUD SNORING)

564
00:47:57.779 --> 00:48:00.147
You're not alone. I'm with you.

565
00:48:00.582 --> 00:48:01.482
(CHUFFS)

566
00:48:07.722 --> 00:48:09.056
(GRUNTS)

567
00:48:09.123 --> 00:48:11.593
The tree would have eaten us
without her.

568
00:48:12.459 --> 00:48:13.460
(SIGHS)

569
00:48:27.642 --> 00:48:32.913
(CREATURES SCREECHING)

570
00:48:36.684 --> 00:48:40.421
(SCREECHING. GRUMBLING)

571
00:49:03.511 --> 00:49:05.547
(WHICKERS)

572
00:49:38.780 --> 00:49:40.447
Bud saved us.

573
00:49:41.749 --> 00:49:45.085
She spit on you to claim you
as part of her family.

574
00:49:50.658 --> 00:49:53.093
Why'd your father
kill your brother?

575
00:50:04.137 --> 00:50:05.673
(SIGHS)

576
00:50:21.756 --> 00:50:23.123
On Earth...

577
00:50:24.291 --> 00:50:26.728
there's a predator known
as the wolf.

578
00:50:26.794 --> 00:50:28.462
It's a powerful creature.

579
00:50:31.198 --> 00:50:32.767
They hunt in packs.

580
00:50:33.233 --> 00:50:34.769
They're very loyal.

581
00:50:35.570 --> 00:50:38.372
The leader of the pack
is the alpha.

582
00:50:38.438 --> 00:50:40.575
Known as the most dominant.

583
00:50:40.842 --> 00:50:42.677
(IN ENGLISH)

584
00:50:42.744 --> 00:50:45.813
(IN YAUTJA)

585
00:50:47.949 --> 00:50:48.950
THIA: No.

586
00:50:49.584 --> 00:50:53.821
The alpha isn't the wolf
who kills the most.

587
00:50:54.856 --> 00:51:00.060
The alpha is actually the one
who best protects the pack.

588
00:52:02.389 --> 00:52:04.626
(FOOTSTEPS LANDING)

589
00:52:18.138 --> 00:52:20.240
Weyland-Yutani synths.

590
00:52:21.809 --> 00:52:25.212
The Kalisk destroyed
most of our mission team.

591
00:52:29.884 --> 00:52:31.786
(GASPS) There I am.

592
00:52:35.790 --> 00:52:36.691
(THUD)

593
00:52:37.290 --> 00:52:38.458
(SIGHS)

594
00:52:47.869 --> 00:52:49.804
(BEEPS)

595
00:52:50.838 --> 00:52:51.873
(WHIRS)

596
00:52:55.009 --> 00:52:57.244
(WHIRRING)

597
00:52:58.412 --> 00:53:01.381
(ELECTRONIC BLIPS)

598
00:53:05.887 --> 00:53:07.254
(CHARGES)

599
00:53:07.320 --> 00:53:09.289
(THUDS)

600
00:53:17.464 --> 00:53:18.866
It's about to be.

601
00:53:25.472 --> 00:53:28.843
Oh. Of course. Right.

602
00:53:31.411 --> 00:53:32.914
Thank you. Dek.

603
00:53:35.449 --> 00:53:37.552
I'm never gonna forget this.

604
00:53:37.985 --> 00:53:39.286
(WHICKERS)

605
00:54:12.620 --> 00:54:15.489
Dek. there's something
I have to tell you.

606
00:54:16.991 --> 00:54:18.626
You need to leave now.

607
00:54:19.694 --> 00:54:22.329
FEMALE ELECTRONIC VOICE:
<i>Location beacon activated.</i>

608
00:54:23.931 --> 00:54:26.067
I called Tessa.
The company is on its way.

609
00:54:26.134 --> 00:54:27.969
You can't be here
when they arrive.

610
00:54:31.839 --> 00:54:32.874
(SIGHS)

611
00:54:33.306 --> 00:54:34.976
So did I. Dek.

612
00:54:35.543 --> 00:54:39.013
The company sent us here
to capture the Kalisk.

613
00:54:48.222 --> 00:54:51.526
Dek. you can't kill it.

614
00:54:56.164 --> 00:54:57.999
I'm sorry. You have to leave.

615
00:54:58.733 --> 00:55:01.334
I needed you
to help bring me here.

616
00:55:08.176 --> 00:55:10.011
I'm trying to help you. Dek.

617
00:55:11.746 --> 00:55:13.648
You think your brother
saved your life

618
00:55:13.714 --> 00:55:15.783
just so you could die here?

619
00:55:24.324 --> 00:55:25.626
(CHUFFS SOFTLY)

620
00:55:33.935 --> 00:55:35.368
(SIGHS)

621
00:55:39.207 --> 00:55:41.441
(CLICKING)

622
00:55:46.514 --> 00:55:48.481
(ELECTRONIC BEEPS. BLIPS)

623
00:56:01.461 --> 00:56:02.997
(SNIFFS)

624
00:56:04.999 --> 00:56:06.734
(WHICKERS)

625
00:56:16.777 --> 00:56:20.848
-(GROWLS)
-(EXPLOSION BOOMS)

626
00:56:22.984 --> 00:56:25.019
(SQUAWKING)

627
00:56:26.087 --> 00:56:28.923
(FOOTSTEPS STOMPING)

628
00:56:29.690 --> 00:56:31.692
(ELECTRONIC CHITTERS)

629
00:56:31.759 --> 00:56:35.428
(RUMBLING APPROACHES)

630
00:56:36.564 --> 00:56:40.167
(THUMPING)

631
00:56:49.911 --> 00:56:51.012
(EXHALES SHARPLY)

632
00:56:52.445 --> 00:56:55.516
(ROARS)

633
00:56:56.017 --> 00:56:58.953
(ROARS INTENSELY)

634
00:57:00.688 --> 00:57:04.125
(SERVOS WHIRRING)

635
00:57:04.191 --> 00:57:06.894
(SNARLS. GRUNTS)

636
00:57:12.633 --> 00:57:13.901
(METALLIC SCRAPE)

637
00:57:14.602 --> 00:57:17.071
(GROWLING)

638
00:57:18.372 --> 00:57:19.640
(GROWLS)

639
00:57:32.687 --> 00:57:35.990
-(PAINED HOWL)
-(PANTING)

640
00:57:36.057 --> 00:57:39.492
(KALISK SNARLS)

641
00:57:39.894 --> 00:57:41.929
(GROWLS)

642
00:57:48.336 --> 00:57:50.137
(GRUNTS)

643
00:57:51.138 --> 00:57:53.674
(WHIRRING)

644
00:57:54.275 --> 00:57:55.509
(GROANS)

645
00:57:55.576 --> 00:57:58.012
Ugh! Come on!

646
00:58:00.081 --> 00:58:02.049
(GROANS)

647
00:58:02.750 --> 00:58:05.485
-(ELECTRICAL CRACKLE)
-(THUDS)

648
00:58:18.165 --> 00:58:19.934
(GROWLS)

649
00:58:20.001 --> 00:58:22.036
(RUMBLING)

650
00:58:30.845 --> 00:58:34.115
-(ROARS)
-(GUNFIRE)

651
00:58:35.483 --> 00:58:37.918
(PAINED GRUNTS)

652
00:58:44.792 --> 00:58:45.793
(SCREAMS) Dek!

653
00:58:45.860 --> 00:58:47.261
-(ROARS)
-(METALLIC CLINK)

654
00:58:48.429 --> 00:58:49.630
(METALLIC WHIRRING)

655
00:58:49.697 --> 00:58:53.834
(GROWLING)

656
00:59:05.546 --> 00:59:07.681
(ROARS)

657
00:59:14.555 --> 00:59:15.956
(PANTING)

658
00:59:22.596 --> 00:59:24.598
(SLOWED METALLIC SCRAPE)

659
00:59:25.099 --> 00:59:26.700
(SNARLS)

660
00:59:29.336 --> 00:59:31.572
(GRUNTS)

661
00:59:33.107 --> 00:59:35.609
(PANTING)

662
00:59:35.676 --> 00:59:38.646
(FLESH SQUELCHING)

663
00:59:41.516 --> 00:59:43.617
(SNARLS)

664
00:59:47.321 --> 00:59:49.190
(CRACKLES)

665
00:59:50.724 --> 00:59:52.326
(SNARLS)

666
00:59:52.393 --> 00:59:53.961
(GRUNTS)

667
00:59:55.696 --> 00:59:57.598
(ROARS)

668
00:59:57.665 --> 00:59:59.133
-(GRUNTS)
-(SNARLS)

669
00:59:59.200 --> 01:00:01.735
(SNIFFING)

670
01:00:08.242 --> 01:00:14.516
(SNIFFS. PURRS)

671
01:00:14.583 --> 01:00:17.084
(BEEPING)

672
01:00:23.090 --> 01:00:24.191
(CHUFFS)

673
01:00:24.925 --> 01:00:26.660
(ROARS. SILENCES)

674
01:00:29.531 --> 01:00:31.533
(STRAINED GRUNTS)

675
01:00:31.600 --> 01:00:33.634
(CRACKLING)

676
01:00:44.745 --> 01:00:46.914
(CHUFFS. SNARLS SOFTLY)

677
01:00:51.586 --> 01:00:55.322
(GRUNTING)

678
01:00:56.357 --> 01:00:58.993
(IN YAUTJA)

679
01:00:59.760 --> 01:01:01.195
(GRUNTS)

680
01:01:02.429 --> 01:01:04.865
(SNARLS)

681
01:01:08.603 --> 01:01:09.703
(GRUNTS)

682
01:01:18.412 --> 01:01:20.214
(GROWLS)

683
01:01:29.624 --> 01:01:33.961
The Yautja cull their weak.
Why were you spared?

684
01:01:36.197 --> 01:01:38.132
(BEEPS. WHIRS)

685
01:01:40.635 --> 01:01:42.469
(THRUMMING)

686
01:01:53.347 --> 01:01:55.115
I read Thia's logs.

687
01:01:56.450 --> 01:01:59.787
You never told her
why your brother protected you.

688
01:02:11.633 --> 01:02:12.933
That's correct.

689
01:02:13.635 --> 01:02:17.572
And you are now property of the
Weyland-Yutani Corporation.

690
01:02:18.272 --> 01:02:21.909
It is a great honor. For you.

691
01:02:22.243 --> 01:02:22.910
(GRUNTS)

692
01:02:22.977 --> 01:02:24.878
(SNARLS. GROWLS)

693
01:02:35.990 --> 01:02:38.225
(FAINT BUZZING)

694
01:02:38.459 --> 01:02:40.494
(BLIPS. BUZZING)

695
01:02:43.264 --> 01:02:47.368
(WHIRRING. ELECTRONIC BLIPS)

696
01:02:54.441 --> 01:02:56.043
(WHISPERING) Tessa.

697
01:02:56.810 --> 01:02:58.078
(CHUFFS)

698
01:02:58.713 --> 01:03:00.314
You made it.

699
01:03:01.683 --> 01:03:03.017
We made it.

700
01:03:07.121 --> 01:03:08.922
I've seen so much.

701
01:03:09.490 --> 01:03:10.824
(THIA EXHALES)

702
01:03:11.258 --> 01:03:15.896
I have so much to tell you.
I saw such incredible creatures.

703
01:03:16.497 --> 01:03:20.100
The Yautja is a great
travelling companion.

704
01:03:21.435 --> 01:03:25.172
Thia.
You were right about the Kalisk.

705
01:03:28.610 --> 01:03:31.412
The creature
is a regenerative miracle.

706
01:03:32.079 --> 01:03:34.315
Humanity will thank us.

707
01:03:37.184 --> 01:03:38.520
We have the Kalisk?

708
01:03:38.586 --> 01:03:39.486
Yes.

709
01:03:40.220 --> 01:03:43.525
And Muthur will be pleased
with your additional catch.

710
01:03:44.659 --> 01:03:45.760
(SNARLS)

711
01:03:45.826 --> 01:03:48.062
(ENRAGED GRUNTING)

712
01:03:48.495 --> 01:03:49.897
(GROWLING)

713
01:03:49.963 --> 01:03:51.566
Additional catch?

714
01:03:51.633 --> 01:03:54.703
(GROWLING. ROARING)

715
01:03:54.769 --> 01:03:55.969
(GRUNTS. SNARLS)

716
01:03:56.036 --> 01:04:00.441
(DEK STRAINING)

717
01:04:00.508 --> 01:04:03.545
The Yautja
is not an ideal specimen.

718
01:04:05.814 --> 01:04:08.916
No. not ideal.

719
01:04:08.982 --> 01:04:14.088
(SNARLS. GRUNTS)

720
01:04:15.590 --> 01:04:17.458
(DEVICE BEEPS)

721
01:04:17.525 --> 01:04:19.993
(SOFT SNARLS)

722
01:04:23.931 --> 01:04:26.166
(DEVICE WHIRS)

723
01:04:28.737 --> 01:04:29.637
(GROWLS)

724
01:04:30.805 --> 01:04:33.641
(HUFFS. GROANS)

725
01:04:33.708 --> 01:04:35.209
(SNARLS)

726
01:04:36.944 --> 01:04:39.246
But its technology is valuable.

727
01:04:40.114 --> 01:04:43.450
We can salvage its weapons
and leave the Yautja.

728
01:04:46.487 --> 01:04:47.622
Good idea.

729
01:04:50.891 --> 01:04:53.127
But it's so malformed.

730
01:04:54.261 --> 01:04:57.331
We're going to need a sample.
For research.

731
01:04:58.566 --> 01:05:00.300
-(BEEPS)
-(AGONIZED ROAR)

732
01:05:00.367 --> 01:05:01.636
(BEEPING)

733
01:05:01.703 --> 01:05:03.337
(DEK SNARLING. GROANING)

734
01:05:03.404 --> 01:05:05.439
(SNARLS. GRUNTS)

735
01:05:08.275 --> 01:05:09.977
He was not the goal
of our mission.

736
01:05:10.043 --> 01:05:12.514
(ELECTRONIC WHIRS)

737
01:05:12.580 --> 01:05:14.516
(GRUNTING)

738
01:05:14.582 --> 01:05:16.383
Tessa. he is deficient.

739
01:05:16.450 --> 01:05:18.419
(SHRIEKING)

740
01:05:18.485 --> 01:05:19.521
Tessa!

741
01:05:22.423 --> 01:05:23.792
(MACHINERY HALTS)

742
01:05:23.858 --> 01:05:25.926
(DEK GRUNTING)

743
01:05:35.302 --> 01:05:39.239
Thia.
this is what is asked of us.

744
01:05:43.711 --> 01:05:46.548
We can be more
than what they ask of us.

745
01:05:50.618 --> 01:05:52.419
What can we be?

746
01:05:54.689 --> 01:05:56.089
Sisters.

747
01:06:12.740 --> 01:06:14.107
Thia.

748
01:06:26.688 --> 01:06:29.757
Do you know why
Muthur gave us feelings?

749
01:06:31.860 --> 01:06:35.195
So we could understand
the creatures on this planet.

750
01:06:37.665 --> 01:06:39.032
(SNARLS)

751
01:06:40.167 --> 01:06:42.670
-And exploit them.
-Exploit them.

752
01:06:43.938 --> 01:06:45.707
The Yautja is different.

753
01:06:45.773 --> 01:06:47.374
(CHUFFS)

754
01:06:48.543 --> 01:06:53.013
He rescued me.
Like you rescued me.

755
01:06:54.516 --> 01:06:57.417
I did not come here
to rescue you.

756
01:06:58.318 --> 01:07:00.655
I am completing our mission.

757
01:07:02.155 --> 01:07:04.358
When we first faced the Kalisk.

758
01:07:05.425 --> 01:07:07.629
I tried to protect you.

759
01:07:09.496 --> 01:07:12.332
And that almost cost me
everything.

760
01:07:14.702 --> 01:07:16.738
What do you mean. Tessa?

761
01:07:17.705 --> 01:07:21.308
I almost made the same mistake
the Yautja's brother made.

762
01:07:21.709 --> 01:07:22.342
(CLICKS)

763
01:07:22.409 --> 01:07:25.445
The weak must be culled.

764
01:07:26.648 --> 01:07:30.284
And Thia. you're broken.

765
01:07:35.122 --> 01:07:36.223
(GRUNTS)

766
01:07:37.692 --> 01:07:40.460
Tessa. incoming message
from Muthur.

767
01:07:40.528 --> 01:07:43.031
Motivate the Yautja
to explain its weapons.

768
01:07:43.096 --> 01:07:44.364
And the unit?

769
01:07:47.535 --> 01:07:48.670
Box her up.

770
01:07:54.107 --> 01:07:55.777
(DOOR HISSES)

771
01:07:59.914 --> 01:08:02.149
(SNARLS. CLICKS)

772
01:08:04.151 --> 01:08:05.452
(HUFFS)

773
01:08:08.322 --> 01:08:11.091
(IN YAUTJA)

774
01:08:14.062 --> 01:08:14.929
(SNARLS)

775
01:08:15.362 --> 01:08:17.565
Why are you speaking
its language?

776
01:08:25.305 --> 01:08:26.608
You heard the orders.

777
01:08:26.674 --> 01:08:29.577
I'm asking it
to explain this device.

778
01:08:31.345 --> 01:08:32.747
What is the device?

779
01:08:33.781 --> 01:08:36.350
(IN YAUTJA)

780
01:08:36.684 --> 01:08:39.386
DEK:

781
01:08:44.324 --> 01:08:46.159
What did it say?

782
01:08:48.062 --> 01:08:49.664
He says it's a map.

783
01:08:50.898 --> 01:08:52.366
How does it work?

784
01:08:59.641 --> 01:09:00.708
(EXPLOSIVE PULSE)

785
01:09:10.051 --> 01:09:11.586
(DOOR BEEPS. HISSES)

786
01:09:12.820 --> 01:09:13.821
(ALARM BLARES)

787
01:09:21.261 --> 01:09:22.462
(CALLS OUT)

788
01:09:22.597 --> 01:09:23.497
Stop!

789
01:09:24.966 --> 01:09:26.333
(THIA STRAINING)

790
01:09:31.238 --> 01:09:34.374
(GRUNTING)

791
01:09:34.809 --> 01:09:36.644
(ROARING)

792
01:09:41.716 --> 01:09:43.751
(ENGINE HUMMING)

793
01:10:01.669 --> 01:10:03.437
(SNARLS)

794
01:10:04.005 --> 01:10:06.841
(GROWLS. CLICKING)

795
01:10:16.349 --> 01:10:19.252
(PANTING)

796
01:10:25.126 --> 01:10:26.661
(GRUNTS)

797
01:10:29.063 --> 01:10:30.464
(WINCES)

798
01:10:48.082 --> 01:10:49.382
(DEVICE BEEPS)

799
01:10:49.449 --> 01:10:50.852
(SHARP GRUNT)

800
01:10:52.486 --> 01:10:54.387
